<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2700">4.4. Setting up the listing scheduler</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>With plentymarkets, you can automatically place listings on the market at a certain time and you can automatically restart finished listings. Use the listing scheduler to set up these automatic procedures. Listings can be linked to several listing schedulers.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want plentymarkets to automatically start listings at a certain time, you have to define time intervals in the listing scheduler. Either select <strong>days of the week</strong> or up to three <strong>days of the month</strong> in the listing scheduler. In both cases, you also have to choose <strong>starting times</strong> for the listing.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the listing scheduler:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Listings » Scheduler</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create new listing scheduler</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as described in <a href="#settings-scheduler">Table 16</a> below.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
